text: Plaque for the installation F.I.S.H. is an outdoor 2009 sculpture depicting a school of fish by Donald Lipski, installed underneath the 1-35 overpass near Camden Street in San Antonio, Texas, United States. The installation features 25 fiberglass resin sculptures of long-eared sunfish, each of which are hand- painted and anatomically correct. One additional fish is displayed inside The DoSeum, a children's museum. The sculpture is part of the collection of Public Art San Antonio. ==See also== * 2009 in art ==References== ==External links== * F.I.S.H. at DonaldLipski.net Category:2009 establishments in Texas Category:2009 sculptures Category:Animal sculptures in Texas Category:Fiberglass sculptures in the United States Category:Fish in art Category:Outdoor sculptures in San Antonio
